## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Scope

This change request upgrades the **kiro-sdlc-agents** VS Code extension to become a superset that bundles the full code-intelligence logic for in-process execution within Kiro IDE. Simultaneously, it introduces a **First-Call Interactive Setup** mechanism for the 3 standalone MCP servers.

### 1.2 Out of Scope

* Rewriting MCP servers in a different language
* Changing the SDLC pipeline workflow logic
* Creating a new MCP server variant
* UI redesign of the VS Code extension beyond the setup wizard
* Authentication/authorization between MCP clients and servers
* Cloud deployment of MCP servers

## 2. Business Requirements

### 2.2 User Stories

| # | Story | Priority |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | In-Process Code Intelligence in Extension | MUST HAVE |
| 2 | First-Call Interactive Setup via MCP Protocol | MUST HAVE |
| 3 | Shared Core Package | MUST HAVE |
| 4 | Standalone MCP Servers for External Clients | MUST HAVE |
| 5 | Clean Separation of Concerns | SHOULD HAVE |
| 6 | Data Migration Between Modes | SHOULD HAVE |
| 7 | Independent Build and Publish | COULD HAVE |

## 3. Dependencies

* mcp-code-intelligence-nodejs v0.6.0
* kiro-sdlc-agents v1.8.1
* MCP Protocol Spec 2024-11-05
* better-sqlite3, onnxruntime-node
* VS Code Extension Host, Node.js >= 20.0.0

## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

* Extension initialization <= 3 seconds
* In-process tool dispatch <= 50ms overhead
* Zero data loss on mode switch
* MCP Protocol 2024-11-05 compliant
* Extension VSIX <= 30MB

